<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="274" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Squiers</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Havana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-27"><hi rend="italic">May 27,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Squiers reports his arrival at Habana on the 26th and reception by
                            the President of Cuba on the 27th of May; that he was the first
                            diplomatic representative to present credentials, and that a most
                            cordial reception was accorded him by the Government and people of
                            Cuba.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>